Mitsubishi Motors Returns to Profit With 4.3 Billion Yen Net

-- B y   A n n a   M u k a i   a n d   Y u k i   H a g i w a r a
-- 
2011-08-01T08:19:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/mitsubishi-motors-returns-to-profit-with-4-3-billion-yen-net.html
Mitsubishi Motors Corp. returned to
profit in the three months ended June 30, aided by selling more
vehicles in  North America ,  Europe  and Asia.  The Tokyo-based automaker posted net income of 4.3 billion
yen ($55.5 million) in the three months ended June 30, compared
with a loss of 11.8 billion yen a year earlier, it said in a
statement today.  Mitsubishi Motors, the maker of the i-MiEV electric car,
raised its half-year profit to break even, from a loss of 10
billion yen announced on June 13. The automaker expects its
retail sales in the six months to Sept. 30 to be at 518,000
units, up 8,000 units from its earlier forecast.  Mitsubishi Motors shares rose 2 percent to 103 yen at the 3
p.m. close of trading in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporters on this story:
